	quests: [
		{
			dependencies: []
			description: [
				"§bMythic Metals§r adds over a dozen new metallic ores across all three dimensions, each with unique properties and progression paths."
				""
				"Ore tiers follow this rough order:"
				"\u2022 §eEarly§r: §6Bronze§r (alloy), §6Carmot§r, §6Aquarium§r (Nether)"
				"\u2022 §eMid§r: §bMythril§r, §bOrichalcum§r, §2Platinum§r"
				"\u2022 §cLate§r: §4Adamantite§r, §dHallowed§r, §fCelestium§r (End)"
				"\u2022 §0Unique§r: §6Prometheum§r (armor grows stronger on kills), §5Stormyx§r (Nether), §eMidas Gold§r"
				""
				"§bAlloy Forgery§r adds the §6Alloy Forge§r multiblock, which is required to smelt alloy metals (Bronze, Durasteel, Quadrillum, etc.) that cannot be smelted in a standard furnace."
				""
				"Most metals use standard furnaces or blast furnaces. Alloys require the Alloy Forge."
			]
			icon: "mythicmetals:mythril_ingot"
			id: "9D00"
			optional: true
			size: 1.5d
			subtitle: "Click to learn more"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9E00"
				title: "Mythic Metals Overview"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "\u2694 Mythic Metals"
			x: 0.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9D00"]
			description: [
				"§6Carmot§r is one of the earliest Mythic Metals ores, found at diamond level in the overworld."
				""
				"Smelt it in any furnace or blast furnace to get §6Carmot Ingots§r. Carmot tools and armor are stronger than iron but lighter \u2014 excellent as an early-mid upgrade before reaching diamond."
				""
				"Carmot ore generates in the overworld at layers Y=64 to Y=-64, with highest density around Y=0. It has a glowing appearance in the world, making it visible at range."
			]
			icon: "mythicmetals:carmot_ingot"
			id: "9D02"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9E02"
				item: "mythicmetals:carmot_ingot"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Carmot"
			subtitle: "Your first mythic metal"
			rewards: [{
				id: "9F02"
				item: "mythicmetals:carmot_ingot"
				count: 4
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -2.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9D00"]
			description: [
				"§6Bronze§r is an alloy of §eCopper§r and §eTin§r, and one of the first metals you can craft using the §bAlloy Forgery§r multiblock."
				""
				"To smelt Bronze, you first need to build an §6Alloy Forge§r \u2014 a multiblock structure made from any type of Forge Controller block (craft with stone bricks) surrounded by specific bricks."
				""
				"Place the §6Forge Controller§r, surround it with §eBricks§r or other valid forge materials, then power it with fuel to begin alloying."
				""
				"Bronze tools and armor sit between stone and iron \u2014 a great early alloy."
			]
			icon: "mythicmetals:bronze_ingot"
			id: "9D03"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9E03"
				item: "mythicmetals:bronze_ingot"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Bronze Alloy"
			subtitle: "Your first alloy forge output"
			rewards: [{
				id: "9F03"
				item: "alloy_forgery:bricks_forge_controller"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 2.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9D03"]
			description: [
				"The §6Alloy Forge§r is a multiblock structure from §bAlloy Forgery§r used to smelt alloy metals that cannot be made in a standard furnace."
				""
				"Build it by placing a §6Forge Controller§r block (crafted with Bricks) and surrounding it with valid forge materials. Different controller materials unlock different alloy recipes."
				""
				"Alloys available include: §eBronze§r (Copper + Tin), §eDurasteel§r (Iron + Manganese), §eQuadrillum§r (multiple metals), and others."
				""
				"The §6Adamantite Block Forge Controller§r is the highest-tier controller, enabling the most powerful alloy recipes."
			]
			icon: "alloy_forgery:bricks_forge_controller"
			id: "9D04"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9E04"
				item: "alloy_forgery:bricks_forge_controller"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Alloy Forge"
			subtitle: "Smelt what furnaces cannot"
			x: 2.0d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9D02"]
			description: [
				"§bMythril§r is a mid-game metal found in the overworld at Y=-16 to Y=-64. It generates as small veins in deepslate."
				""
				"Smelt §6Deepslate Mythril Ore§r in a blast furnace to obtain §6Mythril Ingots§r. Mythril tools and weapons are significantly sharper than diamond \u2014 the sword deals more damage per hit than a Netherite Sword."
				""
				"Mythril armor is lighter than diamond and provides equivalent protection with a subtle agility bonus. It is the recommended mid-game progression metal before reaching Adamantite."
			]
			icon: "mythicmetals:mythril_ingot"
			id: "9D05"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9E05"
				item: "mythicmetals:mythril_ingot"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Mythril"
			subtitle: "Sharper than diamond"
			rewards: [{
				id: "9F05"
				item: "mythicmetals:mythril_ingot"
				count: 4
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -2.0d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9D05"]
			description: [
				"§bOrichalcum§r is a late-mid game metal found at Y=-40 to Y=-64 in the overworld, typically in deepslate."
				""
				"Smelt it in a blast furnace to obtain §6Orichalcum Ingots§r. Orichalcum is primarily used for armor \u2014 the full set provides exceptional protection and grants Haste when all four pieces are worn."
				""
				"Orichalcum tools are competent but the armor is the standout feature. It is an excellent armor tier between Mythril and Adamantite."
			]
			icon: "mythicmetals:orichalcum_ingot"
			id: "9D06"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9E06"
				item: "mythicmetals:orichalcum_ingot"
